<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Atlantic Ocean</emphasis>
: approximately 650 kms west-north-west of the Cape Verde Islands (
<bibRefCitation author="Schellenberg, A" journalOrPublisher="Deutsche Suedpolar-Expedition" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="235 - 414" refId="B170" refString="Schellenberg, A, 1926a. Die Gammariden der Deutschen Suedpolar-Expedition 1901-1903. Deutsche Suedpolar-Expedition 18: 235 - 414" title="Die Gammariden der Deutschen Suedpolar-Expedition 1901 - 1903." volume="18" year="1926 a">Schellenberg 1926a</bibRefCitation>
); west of South Africa (
<bibRefCitation author="Schellenberg, A" journalOrPublisher="Wissenschaftliche Ergebnisse der Deutschen Tiefsee-Expedition auf dem Dampfer &quot; Valdivia &quot; 1898 - 1899" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="193 - 243" refId="B171" refString="Schellenberg, A, 1926b. Amphipoda 3: Die Gammariden der Deutschen Tiefsee-Expedition. Wissenschaftliche Ergebnisse der Deutschen Tiefsee-Expedition auf dem Dampfer &quot;Valdivia&quot; 1898-1899 23: 193 - 243" title="Amphipoda 3: Die Gammariden der Deutschen Tiefsee-Expedition." volume="23" year="1926 b">Schellenberg 1926b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Indian Ocean</emphasis>
: approximately 1100 kms west-north-west of Cocos (Keeling) Islands (
<bibRefCitation author="Birstein, JA" journalOrPublisher="Trudy Instituta Okeanologii" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="152 - 195" refId="B28" refString="Birstein, JA, Vinogradov, ME, 1964. . Trudy Instituta Okeanologii 65: 152 - 195" volume="65" year="1964">Birstein and Vinogradov 1964</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Pacific Ocean</emphasis>
: Kurile-Kamchatka region (
<bibRefCitation author="Birstein, JA" journalOrPublisher="Trudy Instituta Okeanologii" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="401 - 419" refId="B29" refString="Birstein, JA, Vinogradov, ME, 1970. . Trudy Instituta Okeanologii 86: 401 - 419" volume="86" year="1970">Birstein and Vinogradov 1970</bibRefCitation>
); United States, west of California (
<bibRefCitation author="Hendrycks, EA" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Natural History" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="2303 - 2368" publicationUrl="10.1080/00222930210138926" refId="B92" refString="Hendrycks, EA, Conlan, KE, 2003. New and unusual abyssal gammaridean Amphipoda from the north-east Pacific. Journal of Natural History 37: 2303 - 2368, DOI: 10.1080/00222930210138926" title="New and unusual abyssal gammaridean Amphipoda from the north-east Pacific." url="10.1080/00222930210138926" volume="37" year="2003">Hendrycks and Conlan 2003</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Southern Ocean</emphasis>
: Antarctica, approximately 600 kms north of the Oates Coast (
<bibRefCitation author="Birstein, JA" journalOrPublisher="Issledovaniya Fauny Morei" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="33 - 56" refId="B27" refString="Birstein, JA, Vinogradov, ME, 1962. . Issledovaniya Fauny Morei 1 (10): 33 - 56" volume="1" year="1962">Birstein and Vinogradov 1962</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
